  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Campaign to build eco toilets in rural Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigeria is amongst the nations in the world with the highest number of people practicing open defecation, estimated at over 46 million people. Another 56 million people are estimated to be added during the next ten years. The goal is to build twenty eco toilets at targetted public spaces such as; schools, health centres, market centres and motor parks in rural communities within Nigeria. The community-led educational sanitation and hygienic programs.</narrative>
  </description>
